entities.name: Yao application development
entities.description: The process of developing an application using the Yao framework, involving writing DSL, writing processes, and debugging and running the application.

entities.name: Write DSL
entities.description: The task of describing the widget in DSL formats such as Model, API, Table, Form, etc., as part of developing a Yao application.

entities.name: Write Process
entities.description: The task of writing the custom process in TypeScript, JavaScript, or using GRPC plugins as part of developing a Yao application.

entities.name: Debug and Run
entities.description: The task of using the Yao runtime to debug and run the application as part of developing a Yao application.

entities.name: Yao runtime
entities.description: The runtime environment used to debug and run Yao applications.

relationships.description: Writing DSL is a part of developing a Yao application, where the widget is described in DSL formats like Model, API, Table, Form, etc.
Writing the custom process in TypeScript, JavaScript, or using GRPC plugins is a part of developing a Yao application.
Using the Yao runtime to debug and run the application is a part of developing a Yao application.
